Tyrell Malacia has become the first signing of ten Hag era at Manchester United for €15m plus €2m in add-ons to Feyenoord Malacia signed until June 2026   Joshua rejects Fury’s training offer for Usyk rematch     Galtier replaces Pochettino as PSG coach     PSG sack Pochettino after 18 months as coach   Left-back Tyrell Malacia said it is an “incredible feeling” to play for Manchester United after becoming the club’s first signing of the summer transfer window. United, who will fly out to Thailand on Friday for the start of their pre-season tour, made their move for Malacia last Tuesday, hijacking his proposed move to French club Lyon. The Reds struck an agreement with Feyenoord worth £12.9million and have been working to get the deal done in time for the start of the tour ever since.